President Obama has nominated Judge Rainey Ransom Brandt to serve on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Judge Brandt has been serving as a Magistrate Judge in the Criminal Division of the Superior Court since 2013. She has also served as a Magistrate Judge in the Domestic Violence Division in 2012. Prior to her work in the court, Judge Brandt was Special Counsel to the Chief Judge of the Superior Court and taught as a full-time professor in the Department of Justice, Law, and Criminology at American University. She received her J.D. from Catholic University of America's Columbus School of Law and her B.A., M.S., and Ph.D. from American University.